                "tab_content_DyjCdn": {
                  "type": "tab_content",
                  "name": "Tab content",
                  "settings": {
                    "label": "OUR APPROACH",
                    "hash_target": "",
                    "tab_group": "0",
                    "custom_css": "& {\n}",
                    "generate_block_presets": "never",
                    "category_name": "",
                    "hidden_name_backup": ""
                  },
                  "blocks": {
                    "richtext_VVAN7c": {
                      "type": "richtext",
                      "name": "Richtext",
                      "settings": {
                        "title": "<h2><strong>It’s never a single method, only a single goal: absorption.<br/></strong></h2><p>We take a research-first approach to nutrient bioavailability—continuously studying, testing, sourcing, and validating what actually improves absorption in the body. Below are the specific technologies we use—each selected, tested, and applied based on how it measurably improves bioavailability for different types of nutrients.</p><p></p><p><strong>Liposomes:</strong> Liposomes are fat-based spheres that encapsulate nutrients like vitamin C, protecting it from breakdown in the digestive tract.</p><p></p><p><strong>Chelamax®:</strong> Chelating minerals bind a mineral (like magnesium) to an organic molecule such as an amino acid, which “disguises” it as food results in significantly higher absorption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Nusomes®</strong>: A multi-layered vesicle protects active compounds through digestion and use enzyme-triggered, targeted release in the digestive tract to ensure optimal absorption.</p><p></p><p><strong>UltraSol® Technology:</strong> Encapsulates and disperses poorly soluble actives like curcumin into a water-compatible, protective matrix that shields them from degradation in the digestive tract, improving stability and solubility. </p><p></p><p><strong>Fenumat® Technology: </strong>FenuMat® Technology enhances absorption by encapsulating bioactives in a self-emulsifying hybrid hydrogel, protecting actives from degradation in the gut. </p><p></p><p><strong>Capsoil® Nanoemulsions:</strong> Capsoil® nanoemulsions break fat-soluble nutrients into ultra-small, nanometric droplets and coat them with a self-emulsifier, allowing them to fully disperse in water and survive digestion. </p>",
                        "text_alignment": "inherit",
                        "content_class": "richtext-md",
                        "text_color": "",
                        "custom_css": "& h2{\n   margin-bottom: 32px;\n}\n\n\n\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  & h2{\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n}",
                        "hide_if_empty": "none"
                      },
                      "blocks": {}
                    },
